Development is about lifting others up with you, and at Trent, we believe in helping communities become independent & self-reliant and build better futures. Our collaboration with the Bhansali Trust, an organization that actively conducts programs for women empowerment, has helped us establish the Trent Centre at Radhanpur, Gujarat, and sponsor the training of 250 rural women in sewing and embroidery, to upcycle 50% of our garment waste, creating the very stylish ‘Bag of Love’ tote and other accessories. 
Along with employability, the program has also helped these women become financially-independent and foster a sense of sisterhood. Building lives together – what can be more satisfying than that? Shop the tote and other accessories to support the initiative. Visit a Westside store near you, or shop online at westside.com.
